videoSnippet.title: Karoly ruins Mikhail Tal's Brilliancy by NOT playing the Best Moves
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Karoly Honfi vs Mikhail Tal
Sukhumi (1972), Sukhumi URS, rd 14, Sep-02 
Sicilian Defense: Paulsen Variation (B46)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cd4 4. Nd4 e6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 Qc7 7. f4 d6 8. Be3 Be7 9. Qd2 Nf6 10. O-O-O Nd4 11. Bd4 e5 12. Be3 b5 13. fe5 de5 14. Nd5 Nd5 15. ed5 Bd6 16. g4 Bb7 17. Kb1 O-O 18. Bf3 a5 19. Be4 b4 20. Qg2 a4 21. Qh3 g6 22. Bc1 Ba6 23. Rhe1 Bc4 24. Re3 Rfc8 25. Qg2 b3 26. cb3 ab3 27. ab3 Be2 28. Qe2 Qa5 29. Rc3 Qa2 30. Kc2 Rc3 31. Kc3 Bb4 32. Kb4 Qa5 33. Kc4 Qa6

Mikhail Tal had just won the Ilmar Raud Memorial 1972, and nobody knew it yet, but his loss to Gunnar Andreyevich Uusi in round 11 of that event would be his last loss for a very long time. He went undefeated in his next 86 games.1 Now, at the Georgian seaside resort of Sukhumi, Tal faced a diverse field of Soviets and international invitees.

More info on the tournament http://www.chessgames.com/perl/chess.pl?tid=84528
